Database Configuration

Represents a configuration of a database. Includes all settings which have to be made when it comes to the creation of the database. Since the settings are persisted after creation, it must contain a link to the file defined by the interface IConfigureSerializable.

Author:
Sebastian Graf, University of Konstanz
